There does not seem to be a configuration option and I can not find place in the code where it is set.

I've found another question regarding separator, but `output.c:print_separator` does'nt even exists!
</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Sep 2014 06:22:08 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4669/how-can-i-change-the-i3bar-separator/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by Adaephon for &lt;p&gt;Where can I change the &lt;code&gt;|&lt;/code&gt; character used as separator in the i3bar?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There does not seem to be a configuration option and I can not find place in the code where it is set.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I've found another question regarding separator, but &lt;code&gt;output.c:print_separator&lt;/code&gt; does'nt even exists!&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4669/how-can-i-change-the-i3bar-separator/?answer=4676#post-id-4676</link><description>The file `output.c` can be found in the `src` directory of the `i3status` source code. But it does not seem to be an actual pipe symbol when using the i3bar output format, as `print_separator` returns without actually printing anything.

Looking at `i3bar/src/xcb.c:refresh_statusline` in the `i3` code it seems that it is actually a drawn rectangle.</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Sep 2014 10:50:56 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4669/how-can-i-change-the-i3bar-separator/?answer=4676#post-id-4676</guid></item><item><title>Answer by lasers for &lt;p&gt;Where can I change the &lt;code&gt;|&lt;/code&gt; character used as separator in the i3bar?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There does not seem to be a configuration option and I can not find place in the code where it is set.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I've found another question regarding separator, but &lt;code&gt;output.c:print_separator&lt;/code&gt; does'nt even exists!&lt;/p&gt;
